comments: Jokic (DEN) makes marginal body contact with Towns (MIN) after the release of his jump shot attempt.
Covington (MIN) cleanly dislodges the ball at the start of Murray's (DEN) drive.
Barton (DEN) and Wiggins (MIN) engage and disengage off-ball without affecting the other's FOM.
Barton (DEN) makes incidental "high-five" contact with Towns (MIN) after the release of his jump shot attempt.

Okogie (MIN) and Graham (MIN) each make clean contact with the ball as it is dislodged from Murray (DEN) during rebounding. After the ball becomes dislodged, Okogie makes incidental contact with Murray's head. Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.

Okogie (MIN) cleanly dislodges the ball during the hand-off intended for Murray (DEN) and then makes marginal contact with Murray's right side/arm as they each attempt to gain control of the loose ball.

call_type: Turnover: Lost Ball Out of Bounds
comments: After communicating with the Replay Center, it was determined that the ball last touched Murray (DEN) before going out of bounds.
Barton (DEN) makes marginal contact with Wiggins (MIN) that does not affect his SQBR or ability to pass.
Graham (MIN) establishes himself in a screening position in Millsap's (DEN) path and allows him to get around the screen after initial contact takes place.
Millsap (DEN) grasps and then quickly releases Graham's (MIN) jersey without affecting his FOM.
Millsap (DEN) makes marginal body contact with Towns (MIN) after the release of his jump shot attempt.
Wiggins (MIN) makes marginal contact with Barton's (DEN) front and does not affect his SQBR.
Okogie (MIN) makes contact with Murray's (DEN) arm after the release of his jump shot attempt and does not affect his ability to follow through naturally.
Millsap (DEN) makes marginal contact with Graham (MIN) as Graham's momentum naturally carries him across the lane.
Towns (MIN) engages with Jokic (DEN) near the free throw line, but disengages without affecting his FOM.
Covington (MIN) legally contests Murray's (DEN) jump shot attempt and makes incidental "high-five" contact with him after its release.
Craig (DEN) moved laterally into Wiggins' (MIN) path and initiates contact to his side at the end of the drive.
Towns (MIN) makes marginal contact with Jokic's (DEN) left arm and does not affect his ability to defend the inbound.
Craig (MIN) makes marginal contact with Wiggins' (MIN) front that does not affect his SQBR.
Millsap (DEN) makes some body contact with Towns (MIN) after he receives the pass, but it is marginal.
Murray (DEN) makes legal hand-on-ball contact with Okogie (MIN) during the dunk attempt.
Graham (MIN) maintains legal position during Barton's (DEN) driving shot attempt.
Craig (DEN) briefly slides his arm around Towns' (MIN) as they disengage from the pick.
Barton (DEN) maintains a bent forearm to Okogie (MIN) that does not affect his SQBR at the end of the drive or ability to pass.
Jokic (DEN) makes marginal contact with Towns' (MIN) left leg after he returns to the floor following the jump shot attempt.
Graham (MIN) makes marginal body contact with Murray (DEN) after the release of the shot attempt.
Okogie (MIN) makes incidental contact with Barton (DEN) during rebounding and does not affect his ability to retrieve the ball.
Jokic (DEN) makes some contact with Towns' (MIN) backside after the release of the shot attempt, but it is marginal.
Okogie (MIN) initiates contact with Barton's (DEN) side/arm and affects his SQBR as he starts his dribble. Any contact made by Barton to Okogie thereafter is deemed immaterial.
Towns (MIN) extends his foot and initiates contact to the ball in a distinct kicking motion, interfering with the pass' progress.
Barton (DEN) legally contests Covington's (MIN) layup attempt.
Towns (MIN) makes contact with Jokic's (DEN) wrist after the release of his jump shot attempt and does not affect his ability to follow through naturally.
Craig (DEN) and Wiggins (MIN) each engage with one another and make marginal contact that does not affect the other's FOM as the inbound pass is made.
Plumlee (DEN) maintains legal guarding position as Wiggins (MIN) turns and initiates contact to his front at the start of the dribble.
Plumlee (DEN) makes contact to the body of Okogie (MIN) during his shooting motion that affects his jump shot attempt.
